The President announced that John Bryson has resigned as Secretary of the Department of Commerce. He thanked Bryson for his service and praised his efforts in promoting American manufacturing and exports. The President expressed gratitude for Bryson's experience and expertise and stated that he will continue to support the administration's efforts to strengthen the economy. The President also expressed confidence in Dr. Rebecca Blank, who will serve as Acting Secretary, and praised the Commerce Department staff for their work in helping American workers and businesses compete.